Scenario:
You are developing a cross-platform graphics library. The library needs to support various shapes (like Circles and Triangles) that can be drawn using different rendering technologies (Vector or Raster). To avoid a permanent binding between an abstraction (Shape) and its implementation (Renderer), you must decouple them.

Task:

Define an IRenderer interface with a method render(String shapeName).

Implement concrete renderers: VectorRenderer and RasterRenderer.

Create an abstract Shape class that holds a reference to an IRenderer object (the Bridge).

Extend the Shape class to create Circle and Triangle.

In the Main class, demonstrate how a Circle can be rendered using a VectorRenderer and then switched to a RasterRenderer at runtime.